<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF33CEE3FF77F915D96F3426" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF33CEE3FF77F915DBB83B63" blockId="190.[136,778,1732,2056]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF33CEE3FF77F915DA513AF0" bold="true" box="[136,258,1732,1758]" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species in the group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF33CEE3FDAAF914D98B3AF0" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1941" box="[597,728,1733,1758]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="190" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cucutaensis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF33CEE3FDAAF914D98B3AF0" box="[597,728,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="190" pageNumber="191">cucutaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are readily recognized by the apical tegular process obliquely oriented in relation to embolus, reaching 3/4 the size of the bulb.
</paragraph>
